<chapter id="cha.y2.hw">
 <title>Setting Up Hardware Components with &yast;</title>
 <abstract>
  <para>
   &yast; allows you to configure hardware items such as audio hardware,
   your system keyboard layout or printers.
  </para>
 </abstract>
 <note>
  <title>Graphics Card, Monitor, Mouse and Keyboard Settings</title>
  <para>
   Graphics card, monitor, mouse and keyboard can be configured with GNOME
   tools. <phrase os="sled;osuse">See
   <xref
   linkend="sec.gnome.settings.hardware"/> for details.</phrase>
  </para>
 </note>
